# Cursor Rules for uvniche project

## Git Workflow
When the user says "commit & push" or similar variations:
1. Stage all changes with `git add .`
2. Commit to the current dev branch with a descriptive commit message
3. Switch to main branch with `git checkout main`
4. Merge dev into main with `git merge dev`
5. Push main to remote with `git push origin main`
6. Switch back to dev with `git checkout dev`
7. Push dev to remote with `git push origin dev`

This ensures both branches stay synchronized and all changes flow through dev first.

## Project Preferences
- User prefers concise summaries over detailed explanations
- Use shadcn UI components for any UI elements
- Use Inter font for all text elements
- Code suggestions should work with the user's existing API/setup rather than generic examples
- When making changes, always test that the code works immediately

## Development Notes
- This is a Next.js project with Tailwind CSS
- Uses Framer Motion for animations
- Main components: Search component with social links, profile page
- Focus on mobile-first responsive design
- Black background theme with zinc color palette
